## Analysis of Main Target Image

The main target image shows two separate structures:

### Structure 1 (Left Side):
- A standing figure made of orange cylinders and yellow blocks
- 2 layers in total
- Components:
  - Base: Two orange vertical cylinders (standing upright)
  - Middle: One yellow horizontal rectangular block connecting the two cylinders
  - Top: One orange vertical cylinder with a yellow dome/curved cap on top

### Structure 2 (Right Side):
- A more complex structure resembling a small building or house
- 3 layers in total
- Components:
  - Base: A red block with two arches (resembling a bridge)
  - Middle layer: One orange vertical cylinder, two yellow vertical blocks on either side, and one green vertical block at the back
  - Top: An orange triangular roof piece on top of the cylinder

## Selected Blocks from Dictionary

For Structure 1 (Left Side):
- 3 orange cylinders (index 9) - standing vertically
- 1 yellow horizontal rectangular block (index 6)
- 1 yellow dome/cap (index 12)

For Structure 2 (Right Side):
- 1 red block with arches (index 1)
- 1 orange vertical cylinder (index 9)
- 2 yellow vertical rectangular blocks (index 7 and 8) 
- 1 green vertical rectangular block (index 4)
- 1 orange triangular roof piece (index 15)

## Assembly Order

```
{
    Step1: Move block with index 1
    Step2: Move block with index 9
    Step3: Move block with index 7
    Step4: Move block with index 8
    Step5: Move block with index 4
    Step6: Move block with index 15
    Step7: Move block with index 9
    Step8: Move block with index 9
    Step9: Move block with index 6
    Step10: Move block with index 12
}
```

This assembly order first creates the right structure (steps 1-6) and then the left structure (steps 7-10), working from the bottom up in each case.
